  "prompt": "Does sample period, symbol period in Simulink measured in second?",
  "response": "Yes, in Simulink, the sample period and symbol period are typically measured in seconds. \n\nThe sample period (or sample time) refers to the time interval at which the system samples the input signals or updates the outputs. This can be specified in seconds and determines the rate at which the simulation progresses and how often computations are performed.\n\nThe symbol period usually refers to the duration of a single symbol in communication systems. This period is also measured in seconds and represents the time interval during which one symbol is transmitted or received.\n\nBoth periods are fundamental parameters in Simulink models, particularly when dealing with discrete-time systems, communication systems, and digital signal processing. They play a crucial role in establishing how the system operates over time and in synchronizing various components within the model.",
